## Traps

- `gh workflow run` returns the dispatch URL, NOT the resulting
  workflow run ID. The actual run ID can drift in zsh array
  iterations; use `gh run view <id> --json jobs` to confirm which
  package a run was for, never trust array-position labels.
- TestPyPI `400 "Non-user identities cannot create new projects"`
  on a package whose pending publisher exists almost always means
  byte-mismatch (underscore vs hyphen, plural/singular,
  capitalization). The wheel filename uses underscores; the
  publisher form requires hyphens. kaizen-agents tripped this twice
  before the third add stuck.
- Pre-commit `python-use-type-annotations` regex matches any
  `# type` prefix incl. prose — phrase as `# annotations route
  through X`. (Carryover from prior session.)
